# Template for creating new legacy items
# Make a copy of this file for each legacy item you want to create.
#
# Usage:
#   1. Replace:
#        LegacyItemName with the name of the item (e.g. Bloodcrier's Hammer)
#        LegacyItemShortName with the name of the item without special characters and Spaces (e.g. Bloodcrier)
#        LegacyItemSourcePage with the pagenumber of the first page it is found on (will need to be updated on a per ability basis)
#        FirstRitualName, SecondRitualName, ThirdRitualName with the respective Ritual Names of the legacy item (if they have those rituals)
#   2. Adadpt the Tracker Ability "LegacyItemName Tracker":
#        Line 1:
#          Update the "BONUS:VAR|LegacyItemShortNameWielderQualified|1|PREMULT:2,[PRETOTALAB:2],[PREITEM:1,LegacyItemName]" line to match the Wielder Requirements of the Legacy item
#            Exhange "PREITEM" with "PREEQUIP" if you want to only show bonus abilities on the character sheet when the item is actually equipped.
#          Update "BONUS:VAR|LegacyItemShortNameCostLVL|4" to the last level that does not have a personal cost (e.g. 5 if the first cost has to be paid at level 6)
#          At the end of the line, define variables needed for internal item abilities (delete "DEFINE:LegacyItemShortNameEnhancementBonus|0" if your item does not have an enhancement bonus)
#        Line 2-4:
#          Check the BONUS:ABILITYPOOL entries and delete the ones at levels which have no associated costs.
#          In the remaining tags, update the bonus BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|LegacyItemName Personal Cost|1 to the number of cost types paid at the corresponding level (e.g. 2 if there is a Save Penalty and a Hit Point Loss).
#            EXCEPTION! For Skill Point Loss costs grant the number of skill points lost.
#        Line 5:
#          This is Support for the "Replace Legacy Abilities" of the Legacy Champion, use LegacyItemShortNameTotalEnhancement as the enhancement bonus in the item entry below. You can remove this line if the item can't take an armor or weapon enhancement bonus.
#        Line 6-20:
#          These tags grant the individual abilities and boni of the item.
#          Use "PREMULT:2,[PREVARGTEQ:LegacyItemShortNameProgressionLVL,<level>],[!PREABILITY:1...." to grant them whenever a player fulfills all requirements. (The PREABILITY part is needed to allow a replacement by the Legacy Champion's "Replace Legacy Abilities")
#            Increases of enhancement Bonus and weapon/armor properties don't need to include the ",[!PREABILITY:1..." part.
#          Abilities granted at level 11 and level 16 need to also check for the associated legacy feat (e.g. PREMULT:2,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Feat,Lesser Legacy ~ LegacyItemName],[PREVARGTEQ:LegacyItemShortNameProgressionLVL,11])
#   4. Add legacy abilities:
#        Add the listed abilites of the legacy item, using the corresponding type [Extraordinary/Supernatural/SpellLike], replacing "Ability**" with the actual ability name in the entire document ensures that granting ability tags have the matching name
#        Include the "Legacy Daily Use Limit" and "Legacy Command Activated" types in abilities matching that description (required for some legacy item feats)
#        If an ability grants a spell with a save DC, add "LegacyAbilityDC" to the DC calculation (required for the Legacy Focus feat)
#   5. Select Personal Costs:
#        Go through the list of cost abilities and remove the ones that do not apply (most of them).
#   6. Update CostLVL Boni:
#        In the lowest level cost ability, remove the "PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,TYPE.LegacyItemName Cost xy" tag.
#        For the remaining cost abilities, check if there are multiple Personal Costs that have to be paid at the same level. If that is the case, remove the BONUS:VAR|LegacyItemShortNameCostLVL|1 entries of cost abilities higher up in the list for that level.
#          Extend the line with the remaining LVL bonus with a check for the number of abilities on the same level minus one 
#          (e.g. from "PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=Internal,TYPE.LegacyItemName Cost 5" to "PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=Internal,TYPE.LegacyItemName Cost 5,TYPE.LegacyItemName Cost 6" if there are 2 Abilities at level 6)
#        Then check if there is a gap of one or more levels until the next cost has to be paid and update the bonus to match the difference in levels (e.g. if there is a Hit Point Loss at level 6, no cost at level 7, and and Attack Penalty at level 8, the LegacyItemShortNameCostLVL Bonus should be 2).
#        EXCEPTION! Skill Point Loss costs need to grant their CostLVL Bonus outside of the Cost ability.
#                   Add "BONUS:VAR|LegacyItemShortNameCostLVL|<x>|PREVARGTEQ:count("ABILITIES","CATEGORY=Internal","TYPE=LegacyItemName ~ Skill Point Loss <y>"),<z>" to the LegacyItemName Tracker ability (Line 2-4).
#                   Change <x> to the CostLVL Bonus that should be granted, <y> to the level at which the cost should be paid, and <z> to the number of skill points that should be lost.
#        At the lowest level cost abilities after the second and third ritual (i.e. 11+, 17+), also add a requirement of the Lesser/Greater Legacy feats by adding "PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Feat,Lesser Legacy ~ LegacyItemName" to the end of that line (this acts as a reminder for the feat requirement in the costs tab).
#   7. Move Abilities:
#        The entire block from Legacy Tracker to Personal Cost abilities should now be moved into the abilities.lst file of the source you work on.
#   8. Adapt and move the Legacy item:
#        Find the base item of the legacy item from an existing equip.lst file and remove/add properties as needed.
#        Add only the base properties (e.g. the boni without wielder requirements) using EQMODs, and keep the original cost of the mundane weapon (the EQMODs will update the price to match whats in the book).
#        Item properties, such as the item becoming a "Flaming" weapon at a certain level can be added as SPROP based on variables set in the Tracker Ability (e.g. LegacyItemShortNameTotalEnhancement).
#        Once everything has been adapted, move the item line into the equip.lst file of the source you work on.
#   9. Move Legacy Feats:
#        Remove the Greater/Lesser Feats, if the item does not provide bonuses after level 17/11.
#        If you replaced the names in Step 1, the feat lines are ready to be moved into the feats.lst file of the source you work on.
#          Since Legacy Feats can not be gained by class levels, they will not be shown in the feat list and can only be gained via the corresponding ritual template.
#  10. Add Ritual Templates:
#        If you replaced the names in Step 1, temples only need to be extended by the Ritual descriptions.
#        Afterwards, move the template lines into the template.lst file of the source you work on.
#  10. Move Ability Category Templates:
#        If you replaced the names in Step 1, temples only need to be extended by the Ritual descriptions.
#        Afterwards, move the template lines into the template.lst file of the source you work on.

